excerpt: Parklike Buddhist temple known for its enormous statue of storied monk Luang Pu Thuat.
detail_description: Wat Huay Mongkol is a serene Buddhist temple complex located about 15 kilometers west of Hua Hin, Thailand. The highlight of the temple is its enormous statue of Luang Phor Thuad, a revered monk known for his enlightenment and miraculous powers. The statue, standing at 12 meters tall and 10 meters wide, sits atop a large mound and can be seen from afar. Visitors can climb the wide stairway to get closer to the impressive sculpture.
name: Wat Huay Mongkol
address: ทางหลวงหมายเลข 3219, Thap Tai, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

excerpt: Weekend night market with vendors selling art, clothing, decor & handmade goods, plus entertainment.
detail_description: Cicada Market is a vibrant weekend night market in Hua Hin, offering a wide array of art, clothing, decor, and handmade goods from local vendors. It serves as a platform for artists, designers, and creators to connect with tourists and the community through cultural integration. The market features contemporary art in various forms including handmade decorative items, fashion clothes, secondhand items, and innovative SME products. Visitors can also enjoy creative activities such as workshops, exhibitions, performances, dance shows and music.
name: Cicada Market
address: 83, 159 ซอย หัวถนน 21, Nong Kae, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

excerpt: Traditional night marketplace consisting of food vendors & shopping stalls selling clothing & more.
detail_description: Hua Hin Night Market is a vibrant and bustling traditional marketplace located in the heart of central Hua Hin. The market comes alive in the evening, offering a wide array of goods from souvenirs, clothing, and crafts to DVDs.
name: Hua Hin Night Market
address: ซ, Hua Hin 72, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

detail_description: Hua Hin is a coastal town with a vibrant dining scene, offering a wide range of restaurants and bars such as Oceanside beach club & restaurant, Koti Restaurant Huahin, Pa Jua, Let's Sea, and many more. The town is also home to the iconic Hua Hin Railway Station which has retained its original early 1900s-style decor. Visitors can explore the historic station and take in its charming architecture.
name: Hua Hin
address: ถนน สถานีรถไฟ, Hua Hin, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

excerpt: Jungle-themed attraction with waterslides, plus an obstacle course, multiple pools & concessions.
detail_description: Vana Nava Water Jungle is a jungle-themed water park in Hua Hin, Thailand. It features 19 thrilling rides and activities, including The Abyss, Thailand's largest waterslide, and The AquaLoop with fantastic loop-the-loops. In addition to the rides, there are multiple pools, an obstacle course, shops, and fast food restaurants on the premises. This entertainment complex offers lifestyle activities for all ages and has become a significant destination in Thailand's tourism map.
name: Vana Nava Water Jungle
address: 129/99 หมู่บ้านหนองแก, Nong Kae, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

excerpt: Clear-water beach for swimming, with rentable lounge chairs, water sports & amenities nearby.
detail_description: Hua Hin Beach is a popular destination along the Gulf of Thailand, offering clear waters and soft, powdery sand. It's known for its unmatched Thai hospitality and a wide range of exciting activities. The area is not as crowded as other tourist spots, making it perfect for a leisurely day by the sea. Visitors can enjoy water sports like kiteboarding and kitesurfing due to consistent winds. The beach also boasts lovely beachfront hotels with direct access or public areas for relaxation.
name: Hua Hin Beach
address: Prachuap Khiri Khan, Thailand

detail_description: Nestled in the picturesque Hua Hin Hills, Monsoon Valley Vineyard is a surprising gem in Thailand's wine scene. Formerly known as Hua Hin Hills, this vineyard produces new latitude wines, defying traditional norms. The lush tropical paradise of Hua Hin Hills provides a stunning backdrop for over 250 acres of vineyards.
name: Monsoon Valley Vineyard
address: 1 Moo 9 Baankhok Chang Patana, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

excerpt: Lengthy beach for swimming & sunbathing, with various restaurants & temples located nearby.
detail_description: Khao Takiab beach is a 270-meter-long stretch of sandy shoreline located just a 10-minute drive from the lively town of Hua Hin. The beach offers ample opportunities for swimming and sunbathing, and it is surrounded by various restaurants as well as temples. At the top of the road sits Khao Takiab hill, also known as Chopstick Hill, where visitors can escape the tourist crowds and unwind amidst lush hills and quaint temples.
name: Khao Takiab beach
address: Prachuap Khiri Khan, Thailand

excerpt: Large water recreation complex with 9 slides & 7 different types of pools, plus dining facilities.
detail_description: Black Mountain Water Park in Hua Hin is a sprawling water recreation complex spread over 40,000 square meters, just 15 minutes from the town center. It offers an array of attractions including nine slides, a towering vertical slide tower, six pools (including a wave pool that creates the largest waves in Thailand), and a lazy river. The park also features dining facilities and operates with high safety standards and trained lifeguards.
name: Black Mountain Water Park
address: 1 หินเหล็กไฟ 2, Hin Lek Fai, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

detail_description: Hua Hin is famous for its relaxed atmosphere and delectable fresh seafood. The city is a treasure trove of tantalizing street food, offering a wide array of sensory delights to satisfy any craving. From hidden gems tucked away in the city streets to bustling markets, Hua Hin is a paradise for food enthusiasts looking to explore the local culinary scene.
name: Hua Hin
address: Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

excerpt: National reserve area featuring a scenic walkway through a mangrove forest, along with boat rides.
detail_description: Pran Buri Forest Park, situated just a short drive from Hua Hin, is a natural gem boasting an extensive mangrove forest and tropical woodlands. Managed by the Office of Conservation Area Management, this protected area spans 700 rai and features a tranquil white sandy beach. Visitors can explore the diverse ecosystem via raised wooden walkways that wind through the park without disturbing its delicate balance.
name: Pran Buri Forest Park
address: Pak Nam Pran, Pran Buri District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77220, Thailand

excerpt: Hilltop Buddhist temple with a long stairway, a grand, colorful shrine & scenic sea views.
detail_description: Wat Khao Takiap, also known as the 'Temple on the Hill,' is a tranquil Buddhist temple situated just outside Hua Hin, Thailand. It features a lengthy stairway leading to a vibrant shrine and offers picturesque views of the sea. The temple is perched atop a hill and provides breathtaking panoramic vistas of the coastline and its surroundings. At the summit, visitors are welcomed by a majestic golden Buddha statue overlooking the sea, representing tranquility and safety.
name: Wat Khao Takiap
address: 123, 55 Nong Kae-Takiap, Nong Kae, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

detail_description: Klai Kangwon Palace, also known as "Far From Worries Palace," was built in the 1920s as a beach getaway for the Thai royal family. It served as a retreat from the heat of Bangkok and has an interesting history, including being the residence of King Rama VII during a significant political event. Today, it has been transformed into a museum where visitors can explore its art and architecture while enjoying views of the beach and ocean breeze.
name: Klai Kangwon Palace
address: 35 Phet Kasem Rd, Hua Hin, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

detail_description: Hua Hin Hills Winery is situated just a short drive from Hua Hin, surrounded by picturesque vineyards and offering breathtaking views of the countryside. The restaurant serves a delectable array of Thai and Western dishes, complemented by an impressive selection of wines produced on-site.
name: Hua Hin Hills Winery
address: HXC6+J4M, Naresdamri Rd, Hua Hin, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

detail_description: Air Space Hua Hin is a vintage cafe and restaurant with an aviation theme, located within the beachfront community mall. The spacious establishment features two large glass structures serving as a restaurant and a cafe, adorned with aviation-related collectibles and a large plane hanging from the ceiling. Known for its extensive and mouthwatering fusion cuisine, it offers unique and delectable dishes that combine flavors from various cultures.
name: Air Space Hua Hin
address: 12/399 Hua Dorn, Nong Kae, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

detail_description: Khao Hin Lek Fai, also known as Flintstone Hill, is a popular viewpoint near Hua Hin city center. The climb to the top offers stunning panoramic views of Hua Hin and the Gulf of Thailand. Accessible by car or motorcycle with a short walk to the summit, this attraction features paved paths leading to lookout points with metal decks and wheelchair ramps. Visitors can enjoy the beautiful scenery and encounter some monkeys along the way.
name: Khao Hin Lek Fai
address: 527/3 ตำบล หัวหิน หัวเหล็กไฟ, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

excerpt: Scenic setting with a waterfall, fish-filled pools & a series of moderate to challenging hikes.
detail_description: Nestled within the KaengKrachan National Park, about 60 km west of Hua Hin, Pa La-U Waterfall offers a picturesque setting with its 16 cascades and ancient forest teeming with rare wildlife. Visitors can embark on moderate to challenging hikes through unspoiled rainforest to reach the waterfall, where they can marvel at the natural beauty and take a refreshing dip in pools filled with wild carp fish.
name: Pa La-U Waterfall
address: GFQ7+6CV, Huai Sat Yai, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

excerpt: Soft-serve ice cream & signature shakes top the menu at this classic burger & fries fast-food chain.
detail_description: BLUPORT HUA HIN is a unique shopping complex and department store located in the beloved resort town of Hua Hin, Thailand. It offers a delightful mix of shopping, lifestyle, and entertainment experiences in a relaxing resort atmosphere. The design draws inspiration from renowned resort towns around the world, capturing the Mediterranean charm of Cannes and the timeless appeal of Lake Como.
name: BLUPORT HUA HIN
address: 8, 89 Phet Kasem Rd, Nong Kae, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

detail_description: Wat Hua Hin, also known as Wat Amparam, is an ancient temple located in the Hua Hin District of Prachuap Khiri Khan Province. Situated just 2 kilometers from downtown Hua Hin, it dates back to the reign of King Rama V and features various intriguing structures such as the ubosot, coin pavilion, bell tower, chedis, and the revered Grandfather Nakhon Shrine.
name: Wat Hua Hin
address: HX95+X57, Hua Hin, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand

excerpt: This historical tourist attraction celebrates Thai kings with 7 famed statues, a museum & a plaza.
detail_description: Rajabhakti Park, situated on Phetkasem Road in Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan Province, is a historical park paying homage to the royal lineage of Thailand. The park showcases seven striking bronze statues of revered Thai kings from different periods in history.
name: Rajabhakti Park
address: FXX8+H8H, 8 Phet Kasem Rd, Nong Kae, Hua Hin District, Prachuap Khiri Khan 77110, Thailand
